'''Symphony OS''', '''SymphonyOne''' or '''Symphony Linux''', is a [[Live CD]] [[Linux]]-based [[operating system]], developed by [[Ryan Quinn]], [[Jason Spisak]], and [[Alexander Drummond]]. The distribution is currently dormant.<ref>[http://distrowatch.com/table.php?distribution=symphony DistroWatch.com: Symphony OS]</ref>
When it started, Symphony OS was based on [[Knoppix]]. Since its May 2006 release it is no longer based on Knoppix, but rather on [[Debian]] unstable, and features a functional hard drive installer. Symphony OS 2007 Preview, was based on [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] 7.04.<ref>[http://symphonyos.com/cms/?p=15 Symphony OS 2007 Preview]</ref>SymphonyOne was released on [[April 1]], 2008. The release of version 2008.1 is based on Ubuntu 7.10.
